    {
      "d": "ltr",
      "words": [
        {
          "w": "Note that in this plural form, the singular has short \"a\" before the \"t\" (muslimat-u-n), and the \"t\" is round (ة), whereas in the plural the \"a\" is long(muslimaat-u-n), and the \"t\" is open (ت) \n\n The broken plural: There are more than twenty patterns of the broken plural. Some are given here. Unlike in English, the broken plural is very widely used in Arabic. These are:"
